name: Double Six Beach
description: Relaxed beach popular with travelers offering umbrella rentals, live music & a chill ambiance.

name: Waterblow
description: When waves crash at high tide into this reef, the resulting splash can tower up to 26 feet high.

name: Sanur
description: Colorful fishing boats dot beaches of this resort town with galleries, restaurants & an old temple.

name: Prama Sanur Beach Hotel Bali
description: Upscale beachfront property with a spa & open-air dining, plus outdoor pools for adults & kids.

name: Badung Market
description: Traditional open-air market with a variety of offerings, including groceries, clothing & souvenirs.

name: Sukawati Art Market
subtypes: Clothing wholesale market place, Tourist attraction
description: Colorful marketplace with merchants selling apparel, jewelry, locally made souvenirs & more.

name: Pasar Senggol Gianyar
description: Night market on main strip with stalls/vendors selling Indonesian street food, clothing & souvenirs.

name: beachwalk Shopping Center
description: Chic open-air mall with popular international chain stores, restaurants & a central garden.

name: Uluwatu Temple
subtypes: Hindu temple, National reserve, Performing arts theater, Tourist attraction
description: Perched on a cliff, this ancient Hindu temple features ocean views & hosts traditional dance shows.

name: Ulun Danu Beratan Temple
description: Scenic Hindu temple on a lake with gardens, boating & wild animals for photo opportunities.

name: Mal Bali Galeria
description: Dynamic retail hub with department stores, boutiques, a supermarket, eateries & a movie theater.

name: Discovery Mall Bali
description: Beachfront shopping complex offering department stores, boutiques, restaurants & cultural events.

name: Campuhan Ridge Walk
description: Lush, scenic locale known for its mellow hiking trails & sweeping hilltop views.

name: Kajeng Rice Field
description: Track taking walkers through rice fields & Kajeng village, joining another path for a circular walk.

name: Sacred Monkey Forest Sanctuary
description: Hindu temple complex set in the jungle, renowned for the macaque monkeys who call it home.

name: Bali Zoo
subtypes: Zoo, Animal park, Nature preserve, Tourist attraction
description: Large zoo featuring orangutans, elephants & African lions, plus interactive encounters & shows.

name: Kebun Raya Bali
description: Sprawling botanical gardens with diverse tree, plant & bird species, plus a greenhouse & lake views.

name: Bali Swing
subtypes: Theme park, Outdoor activity organiser, Tourist attraction
description: Adventure outfit offering a range of tours, rafting trips & rope swings with jungle views.

name: Bali Botanical Garden
description: Sprawling botanical garden with local tropical plants & wildlife, plus a treetop ropes course.
